In 2000, the racial makeup of the town was 82.85% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 15.41% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.77% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], and 0.96% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 0.58% of the population. By 2020, its racial and ethnic makeup was 80.13% non-Hispanic white, 15.63% African American, 0.45% Native American, 3.13% mixed, and 0.67% Hispanic or Latino of any race.<ref name=":0" />

